<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1903-11-04T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1903-11-04T00:00:00-05:00" n="294" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d294">
                        <head>[Untitled]</head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Colon</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1903-11-04"><hi rend="italic">November 4,
                                1903</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p rend="flushleft"><hi rend="smallcaps">Secretary of the Navy</hi>, <hi rend="italic">Washington, D. C.:</hi></p>
                        <p>Government troops yet in Colon. Have prohibited transportation of troops
                            either direction. No interruption of transit as yet. Will make every
                            effort to preserve peace and order.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hubbard.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>